<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-simplifying-rational-expressions" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Simplifying Rational Expressions</title>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>Recall that simplifying a fraction involves cancelling the greatest common factor from the numerator and the denominator, so the fraction is in <term>lowest terms</term>.</p>
    <example>
      <title>Simplifying a Numerical Fraction</title>
      <statement>
        <p>To simplify <m>\dfrac{36}{60}</m>, factor both the numerator and denominator,</p>
        <md>
          <mrow>\dfrac{36}{60} \amp = \dfrac{2 \times 2 \times 3 \times 3}{2 \times 2 \times 3 \times 5}</mrow>
        </md>
        <p>Cancel the common factors from the numerator and denominator,</p>
        <md>
          <mrow>\dfrac{\cancel{2} \times \cancel{2} \times \cancel{3} \times 3}{\cancel{2} \times \cancel{2} \times \cancel{3} \times 5} \amp = \dfrac{3}{5}</mrow>
        </md>
      </statement>
      <p>Therefore, <m>\dfrac{36}{60}</m> simplifies to <m>\dfrac{3}{5}</m>.</p>
    </example>
    <p>Similarly, simplifying a <term>rational expression</term> involves factoring the numerator and denominator, and <alert>cancelling common factors</alert> until there are no common factors other than 1. In this case, we say the rational expression is in <term>lowest terms</term>.</p>
  </introduction>
  
  <subsection xml:id="subsection-simplifying-monomials">
    <title>Simplifying Expressions with Monomials</title>
    
    <project xml:id="project-monomial-expressions">
      <title>Monomial Expressions</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Simplify each rational expression, and state any restrictions on the variables.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{12x}{48x^3}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{1}{4x^2}, x\neq 0</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{21ab}{35ab^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{3}{5b}, a\neq 0, b\neq 0</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{8m^2n}{24mn^3}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{m}{3n^2}, m\neq 0, n\neq 0</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{16x^3y^3}{36x^5y^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{4y}{9x^2}, x\neq 0, y\neq 0</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{12a^2b^3}{40a^3b}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{3b^2}{10a}, a\neq 0, b\neq 0</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{6xyz^3}{3x^2y^2z}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{2z^2}{xy}, x\neq 0, y\neq 0, z\neq 0</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{8x}{14y}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{4x}{7y}, y\neq 0</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{15xy}{24x}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{5y}{8}, x\neq 0</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{12ab}{6a^2b^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{2}{ab}, a\neq 0, b\neq 0</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{7x^3}{21x^8}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{1}{3x^5}, x\neq 0</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{4x^2yz^5}{6x^2y^3z^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{2z^3}{3y^2}, x\neq 0, y\neq 0, z\neq 0</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{30x^4y^3}{-6x^7y}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>-\dfrac{5y^2}{x^3}, x\neq 0, y\neq 0</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{9x^2}{6x^3}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{3}{2x}, x\neq 0</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{7a^2b^3}{21a^4b}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{b^2}{3a^2}, a\neq 0, b\neq 0</m></answer>
      </task>
    </project>
    
    <p>Sometimes, factors can have more than one term in them.</p>
    
    <project xml:id="project-binomial-factors">
      <title>Binomial Factors</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Simplify each rational expression, and state any restrictions on the variables.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{6(x+2)}{10(x+2)}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{3}{5}, x\neq -2</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{(x+1)(x-1)}{(x-1)^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{x+1}{x-1}, x\neq 1</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{5(x+3)}{(x+3)(x-3)}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{5}{x-3}, x\neq -3,3</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{(x-1)(x-3)}{(x+2)(x-1)}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{x-3}{x+2}, x\neq -2,1</m></answer>
      </task>
    </project>
  </subsection>
  
  <subsection xml:id="subsection-factoring-polynomials">
