  <subsection xml:id="subsection-common-mistake">
    <title>Common Mistake: Cancelling <q>Common Terms</q></title>
    <p>Common factors can be cancelled, but not <q>common terms</q>. For example,</p>
    <md>
      <mrow>\dfrac{x + 1}{x} \amp = \dfrac{\cancel{x} + 1}{\cancel{x}} \amp\amp \text{$x$ is not a factor of the numerator}</mrow>
      <mrow>\dfrac{x^2 + x + 3}{x^2 + 3} \amp = \dfrac{\cancel{x^2} + x + \cancel{3}}{\cancel{x^2} + \cancel{3}} \amp\amp \text{$x^2$ and $3$ are terms, not factors, so they can't be cancelled}</mrow>
      <mrow>\amp \amp\amp \text{(This expression is already in lowest terms)} \notag</mrow>
      <mrow>\dfrac{x - 2}{x + 1} \amp = \dfrac{\cancel{x} - 2}{\cancel{x} + 1} \amp\amp \text{$x$ is a term, not a factor}</mrow>
      <mrow>\dfrac{2x^2 - 9}{2x - 3} \amp = \dfrac{\cancelto{x}{2x^2} - \cancelto{3}{9}}{\cancel{2x} - \cancel{3}} \amp\amp \text{$2x^2$, $2x$, $9$, and $3$ are all terms, not factors}</mrow>
      <mrow>\dfrac{x^2 + 2x + 1}{x^2 + 3} \amp = \dfrac{\cancel{x^2} + 2x + 1}{\cancel{x^2} + 3} \amp\amp \text{$x^2$ are both terms, not factors}</mrow>
    </md>
    <p>In other words, something must be a factor of the <em>entire</em> numerator in order to cancel them.</p>
  </subsection>
  
  <subsection xml:id="subsection-summary">
    <title>Summary of Simplifying Rational Expressions</title>
    
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p><alert>Factor the numerator and denominator as much as possible</alert> (if there are multiple terms, with addition or subtraction).
          <ul>
            <li>If there is multiplication only, there is no factoring needed.</li>
          </ul>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p><alert>Cancel common factors</alert>.
          <ul>
            <li>Remember: only factors can cancel (not terms, which are added or subtracted).</li>
            <li>Sometimes, common factors will differ by a constant factor like <m>-1</m>.</li>
          </ul>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li><alert>Rewrite the fraction</alert>, with what's left after cancelling.</li>
      <li><alert>Find restrictions</alert> (if needed). Find the values of the variable that make the denominator 0 (from the original denominator, before any cancellation).</li>
    </ol>
  </subsection>
  
  <subsection xml:id="subsection-word-problems">
    <title>Word Problems</title>
    
    <example>
      <title>Isosceles Triangle</title>
      <statement>
        <p>An isosceles triangle has two sides of length <m>9x+3</m> and a perimeter of <m>30x+10</m>, determine the ratio of the base to the perimeter in simplified form and state the restriction on <m>x</m>, then explain in one sentence why that restriction is necessary in this situation.</p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p><m>\dfrac{b}{P}=\dfrac{12x+4}{30x+10}=\dfrac{2}{5}</m>, restriction <m>x\gt-\dfrac{1}{3}</m> because the side lengths and perimeter must be positive (at <m>x=-\dfrac{1}{3}</m> they are zero).</p>
      </answer>
    </example>
    
    <example>
      <title>Rectangle Ratio</title>
      <statement>
        <p>A rectangle is six times as long as it is wide, determine the ratio of its area to its perimeter in simplest form if its width is <m>w</m>.</p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <m>\dfrac{A}{P}=\dfrac{6w^2}{14w}=\dfrac{3w}{7}</m>
      </answer>
    </example>
    
    <example>
      <title>Equivalent Rational Expressions</title>
      <statement>
        <p>The quotient of two polynomials is <m>3x-2</m>, give two examples of a rational expression equivalent to this polynomial that has the restriction <m>x\neq 4</m>.</p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p><m>\dfrac{(3x-2)(x-4)}{x-4}</m> and <m>\dfrac{(3x-2)(x-4)^2}{(x-4)^2}</m> (each simplifies to <m>3x-2</m> for <m>x\neq 4</m>).</p>
      </answer>
    </example>
    
    <example>
      <title>Consecutive Restrictions</title>
      <statement>
        <p>Give an example of a rational expression that could have three restrictions that are consecutive numbers.</p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>e.g. <m>\dfrac{x^2+1}{(x-2)(x-3)(x-4)}</m> (restrictions <m>x\neq 2,3,4</m> are consecutive).</p>
      </answer>
    </example>
    
    <example>
      <title>Box Dimensions</title>
      <statement>
        <p>The volume of a box is given by <m>(6x^2+23x+21)(x+5)</m> and its height is <m>2x+3</m>. Find a simplified expression for the area of the bottom of the box.</p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <m>A=\dfrac{(6x^2+23x+21)(x+5)}{2x+3}=(3x+7)(x+5)</m>
      </answer>
    </example>
  </subsection>
  
  <subsection xml:id="subsection-two-variables">
    <title>Simplifying with Two Variables</title>
    
    <project xml:id="project-two-variable-expressions">
      <title>Two Variable Expressions</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Simplify each rational expression.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{x^2-xy}{x^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{x-y}{x}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{x^3}{x^3+x^2y}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{x}{x + y}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{x^2y+xy^2}{xy+y^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{4a^2b-2ab^2}{(2a-b)^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{2ab}{2a-b}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{-5x^3y^2}{10xy^3}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>-\dfrac{x^2}{2y}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{5ab}{15a^4b-10a^2b^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{1}{a(3a^2-2b)}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{2ab-6a}{9a-3ab}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>-\dfrac{2}{3}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{x^2+2xy-3y^2}{2x^2-xy-y^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{x+3y}{2x+y}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{x^2-3xy+2y^2}{x^2-4y^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{x-y}{x+2y}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{4x^2 - 4y^2}{x^2 - 2xy + y^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{4(x+y)}{x-y}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{6-x-2x^2}{12+7x-10x^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{x+2}{5x+4}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{15+x-2x^2}{21-10x+x^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>-\dfrac{2x+5}{x-7}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{xy+4x-y-4}{xy+4x-4y-16}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{x-1}{x-4}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{xy-3x+2y-6}{xy+5x+2y+10}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{y-3}{y+5}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{4x^2-16y^2}{x^2+xy-6y^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{4(x+2y)}{x+3y}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{4x^2y-2xy^2}{(2x-y)^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{2xy}{2x-y}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{x^2-7xy+10y^2}{x^2+xy-6y^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{x-5y}{x+3y}</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{2x^2-xy-y^2}{x^2-2xy+y^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>\dfrac{2x+y}{x-y}</m></answer>
      </task>
    </project>
    
    <project xml:id="project-restrictions-two-variables">
      <title>Restrictions with Two Variables</title>
      <introduction>
        <p>Find the restrictions, if any, on each rational expression.</p>
      </introduction>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{x^2+y^2}{x^2-y^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x\neq y,-y</m></answer>
      </task>
      <task>
        <statement><m>\dfrac{x-y}{x^2-2xy+y^2}</m></statement>
        <answer><m>x\neq y</m></answer>
      </task>
    </project>
  </subsection>
  
